  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Instagram does not provide a feature that allows you to see who has viewed your profile. Any third-party apps or websites claiming to offer this functionality are likely scams or violate Instagram's terms of service, potentially compromising your account security.\n\nHere are some legitimate ways to gauge engagement on Instagram:\n\n1. **View Story Insights**: If you have a public account or a business/creator account, you can see who viewed your Instagram Stories. Simply swipe up on a Story to check the viewers.\n\n2. **Check Post Insights**: Business and creator accounts can access insights for posts, Stories, and Reels, showing metrics like likes, comments, shares, and profile visits.\n\n3. **Profile Visits**: Business and creator accounts can see how many people visited their profile in the last 7 or 30 days, but not specific usernames.\n\n4. **Engagement Metrics**: Monitor likes, comments, and direct messages to understand who is interacting with your content.\n\nIf Instagram introduces a feature to track profile viewers in the future, it will likely be announced officially through their app or blog. Always prioritize your account security and avoid using unauthorized third-party tools.",
